<subSubSection id="070DE0D727FE2E38C54B338B29D75B2D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="D616C4AD94446C0652908B6B24519AAF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6DF80FEDD08735910108C8502522506E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="3EB0243B0D6505D1265D19C71F75B907" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="2B0CBEF907ACA1AE0C62E5F9715A408D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the branched, well-developed cymes with long peduncles, large leaves and somewhat campanulate corolla. From 
<taxonomicName id="4D0E8CF2516177C956CA08540924006A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="batatoides">
<emphasis id="1C0A417BD2C233CE257ACC03031B4E5A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. batatoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is distinguished by the longer sepals and larger leaves which are undulate and often somewhat angled, almost with a lateral tooth, hence 
<normalizedToken id="615D6F013F402D02EAE7CB2994E61FFA" originalValue="Choisy’s">Choisy's</normalizedToken>
varietal name of 
<taxonomicName id="C082D41DB19A4AC18F16E24B7A6DC912" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis id="7828E4768EC86486164D5E25B58CA18A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C7C1387E8D9BA5065FC044AD3F680D3A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This has been identified as 
<taxonomicName id="8ECB0609A9B71B17E54A4E1ECF04FC4D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="73B5E5E2AB3367305DDADB479EEFEB7A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, perhaps because Choisy treated 
<taxonomicName id="C5CAF1AD2AB05CFD0D8C992195535278" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="0AF0FAF9FDB478458E9EB24E5B5E6880" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="CD68844B6D4612CF27E57650CEA1EC60" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="batatoides" variety="angulata">
<emphasis id="50BF62F8EC07084F4EB69521A94EC8CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. batatoides</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="11DCDDDBF3FB0CC9BE87164C10838DDF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="B557C87079A17B520503B8F49A2319F2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="D1578468CE2149278973387BAB107D32" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a quite different cerrado species whereas 
<taxonomicName id="2BB72634E7B7DAAE599301A133F84FA9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austrobrasiliensis">
<emphasis id="99D59D4A6AE22C3DF855E97F76EF75B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. austrobrasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a plant of the Atlantic forests of southern Brazil and has not been found in the cerrados of 
<normalizedToken id="204B9AB62BC3FC4E3CD262D744EDD0CC" originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
or further north in Brazil. Plants called 
<taxonomicName id="438CB4D5549617702E3EA068D613CBDE" authority="(Simao-Bianchini et al. 2016)" baseAuthorityName="Simao-Bianchini" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="A2BD4ABA7982DDB50F7DAAE67C57AFFD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea goyazensis</emphasis>
(
<normalizedToken id="53C66C9307170D2A2AD0EA808F6E32A6" originalValue="Simão-Bianchini">Simao-Bianchini</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016)
</taxonomicName>
are a mixture of 
<taxonomicName id="980ADF76A755F1F75D932A5E6294156E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austrobrasiliensis">
<emphasis id="04446257C71C4AF777BDF1E4BC7C7DB7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. austrobrasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and glabrous forms of 
<taxonomicName id="BAD9EE68D823D2B17F1713F2007E6DB8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">
<emphasis id="688B930AC8B5BF5499467E9BF581DD53" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. goyazensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
